main event: A civilian reported seeing a fast-moving satellite (ECHO II) above the horizon in Preble County, Ohio on March 26, 1966.
interesting points: The object was seen moving at high speed while the witness described its appearance as a bright star., The sighting lasted approximately three minutes., The object was observed while the weather was clear., No physical evidence or photographs were collected during the observation., The report is part of the Project Blue Book documentation.
